Azure Cloud Shell is a browser-based command-line environment accessible directly from the Azure Portal.

It supports:

* Bash
* PowerShell
* Azure CLI
* Persistent storage

For example, users can manage resources without installing local tools.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is remote administration from any device.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is quick troubleshooting sessions.

Cloud Shell improves portability and operational convenience.
